WEBVTT

00:00.064 --> 00:01.524
<i>Previously on "Suits"...</i>

00:01.526 --> 00:03.578
<i>Rachel,</i>
<i>it's Professor Dunbar.</i>

00:03.679 --> 00:05.657
I was wondering if you'd
be interested in helping me

00:05.681 --> 00:07.114
<i>with the Innocence Project.</i>

00:07.149 --> 00:09.094
You want me to help you get
an innocent man off death row?

00:09.118 --> 00:10.084
<i>What do you want, Harvey?</i>

00:10.119 --> 00:11.418
Help me protect Mike Ross.

00:11.454 --> 00:12.564
He's in there
with a guy I put away,

00:12.588 --> 00:13.554
and the guy is no joke.

00:13.589 --> 00:14.955
What am I supposed to do?

00:14.991 --> 00:17.224
You're supposed to move
the guy to another prison.

00:17.259 --> 00:18.826
You want me one-on-one?
You got it.

00:18.861 --> 00:20.794
I'm gonna use this,
and they're gonna hold you.

00:20.830 --> 00:22.162
- No!
- What's going on here?

00:23.766 --> 00:25.165
Why'd you come back
with a guard?

00:25.201 --> 00:26.712
I didn't do it
to get you to forgive me.

00:26.736 --> 00:28.780
I never should have let him
in here in the first place.

00:28.804 --> 00:30.537
The time you served
while awaiting trial

00:30.573 --> 00:32.473
was never factored
into your sentence.

00:32.508 --> 00:34.274
You're eligible for
parole in six weeks.

00:34.310 --> 00:36.410
You think I don't know
this is your protector's idea

00:36.445 --> 00:37.544
to get me off your back?

00:37.580 --> 00:38.812
Nah, Frank.

00:38.848 --> 00:41.248
Harvey's idea was for me
to tell these guys

00:41.283 --> 00:42.449
that you're an informant.

00:42.485 --> 00:44.351
I figured out a way
to get Mike out early.

00:44.387 --> 00:45.352
What's the catch?

00:45.388 --> 00:46.687
He has to inform
on his roommate.

00:46.722 --> 00:48.222
Mike gets him to turn,
he's free.

00:48.257 --> 00:49.490
When do you need an answer by?

00:49.525 --> 00:50.624
Yesterday.

00:50.660 --> 00:51.959
And the answer needs to be yes.

00:54.930 --> 00:55.963
Harvey, wait a second.

00:55.998 --> 00:56.964
Where are you going?

00:56.999 --> 00:58.143
Where do you think I'm going?

00:58.167 --> 00:59.199
I'm gonna see Mike.

00:59.235 --> 01:00.612
And I know what
you're going to say,

01:00.636 --> 01:02.703
but Mike went to prison
so we wouldn't have to,

01:02.738 --> 01:04.971
and now he's in danger
from a guy I put away.

01:05.007 --> 01:07.341
So you'll forgive me if
I don't stand around and wait

01:07.376 --> 01:08.776
for you to drop the hammer.

01:08.811 --> 01:11.211
You think I like the idea
of him rotting in that place?

01:11.247 --> 01:12.713
But if you want
this thing to work,

01:12.748 --> 01:14.893
you can't go running up there
in the middle of the night.

01:14.917 --> 01:16.850
You heard Cahill.
He needs an answer yesterday.

01:16.886 --> 01:18.886
What he needs is results.

01:18.921 --> 01:20.699
And if Mike's lawyer
pulls him out of his cell

01:20.723 --> 01:22.467
in the middle of the night,
then his roommate

01:22.491 --> 01:24.124
is going to sense
there's something wrong

01:24.160 --> 01:26.894
before this thing
even gets started.

01:26.929 --> 01:29.830
Fine, but I'm going up there
first thing in the morning,

01:29.865 --> 01:32.332
and nothing you say
is going to stop me.

01:40.376 --> 01:41.742
Can't sleep?

01:41.777 --> 01:43.210
Not really.

01:43.245 --> 01:44.778
Well, as long as you're up,

01:44.814 --> 01:45.779
might want to think about

01:45.815 --> 01:47.681
putting up some
pictures of your own.

01:47.717 --> 01:50.851
That way, you won't have
to keep staring at mine.

01:54.790 --> 01:57.925
How old are they?

01:57.960 --> 02:00.594
Maddy is seven.

02:00.629 --> 02:03.263
Nate just turned five.

02:03.299 --> 02:05.499
They look really sweet.

02:05.534 --> 02:08.869
Yeah...they're great.

02:08.904 --> 02:10.704
How often do you
get to see 'em?

02:10.740 --> 02:12.250
- I don't.
- What do you mean you don't?

02:12.274 --> 02:13.240
Bad divorce or something?

02:13.275 --> 02:15.008
Nah, nah,
nothing like that.

02:15.044 --> 02:16.844
We've been married
for ten years.

02:16.879 --> 02:18.390
I just--I just don't
let 'em come here.

02:18.414 --> 02:19.613
What?
Why not?

02:19.648 --> 02:21.515
They shouldn't see
their father as a criminal.

02:21.550 --> 02:22.516
Kevin, come on, man.

02:22.551 --> 02:23.717
I know it's hard on them.

02:23.753 --> 02:25.652
It tears me up every
single day that I'm here.

02:25.688 --> 02:29.156
But they're kids.
They're resilient.

02:29.191 --> 02:30.758
Yeah, I wouldn't be so sure.

02:30.793 --> 02:32.092
Well, Mike,
you don't have kids.

02:32.128 --> 02:33.128
So you don't know.

02:33.162 --> 02:34.461
No.
I don't.

02:34.497 --> 02:37.264
But I do know what it's like
to be a kid missing his dad.

02:37.299 --> 02:40.467
Please don't tell me your
old man abandoned the family.

02:40.503 --> 02:45.305
Both of my parents died
in a car accident when I was 11.

02:45.341 --> 02:47.307
Hit by a drunk driver.

02:47.343 --> 02:50.444
Jesus, that's...
I'm sorry, Mike.

02:52.348 --> 02:55.549
Yeah, it was a long time ago.

02:55.584 --> 02:57.384
Kevin, I understand
the instinct to protect

02:57.419 --> 02:59.887
your children, but what are
you protecting them from?

02:59.922 --> 03:01.188
What do you mean?

03:01.223 --> 03:02.956
I mean we've been
roommates for a while now.

03:02.992 --> 03:06.093
Don't you think it's time you
told me what you're in here for?

03:07.696 --> 03:09.029
Hey, Ross.

03:09.064 --> 03:10.130
Your lawyer's here.

03:10.166 --> 03:11.665
- Now?
- I'm just the messenger.

03:11.700 --> 03:13.667
You want out of this box or not?

03:15.000 --> 03:21.074
