03:34.356 --> 03:36.190
Mr. Bailey, my name
is Rachel Zane.

03:36.225 --> 03:37.791
I am a law student at Columbia,

03:37.827 --> 03:39.626
and I'm here to talk
to you about your case.

03:39.662 --> 03:40.794
Student?

03:40.830 --> 03:42.763
Yes, we work alongside
the Innocence Project

03:42.798 --> 03:44.810
to determine if you have
the criteria for an appeal.

03:44.834 --> 03:47.634
Do you know how long
I've been sittin' on death row?

03:47.670 --> 03:49.636
12 years.
I read your file.

03:49.672 --> 03:52.206
And for the last ten of 'em,
I've been writing letters

03:52.241 --> 03:55.943
and begging any lawyer
to listen to my story.

03:55.978 --> 03:59.213
And they finally get around
to getting back to me,

03:59.248 --> 04:01.081
and they don't even
have the courtesy

04:01.116 --> 04:03.016
of sendin' me a real lawyer?

04:03.052 --> 04:06.386
Mr. Bailey, trust me,
I will fight for you.

04:06.422 --> 04:08.522
You're a student.

04:08.557 --> 04:11.859
You can't do shit for me.

04:11.894 --> 04:14.428
Well, you know what?
You killed two people.

04:14.463 --> 04:16.829
In cold blood.

04:16.866 --> 04:19.233
You know it, and I know it,
and that's why you're in there,

04:19.267 --> 04:20.934
so thank you
for making the decision

04:20.970 --> 04:23.871
to not take your case
an easy one.

04:23.906 --> 04:25.205
You don't know me.

04:25.241 --> 04:29.343
All you know is what you
read in some damn file.

04:29.378 --> 04:31.478
I didn't kill anyone.

04:31.513 --> 04:34.314
I've been saying it for 12 years
and I can prove it.

04:34.350 --> 04:35.315
You're right.

04:35.351 --> 04:36.516
I don't know you.

04:36.552 --> 04:39.186
And you don't know me either.

04:39.221 --> 04:43.357
So do you want to take
a chance on each other or not?

04:43.392 --> 04:48.262
I need help, Ms. Zane.

04:49.765 --> 04:52.199
So let me help you.

04:56.438 --> 04:57.738
Harvey, what are
you doing here?

04:57.773 --> 04:59.573
There's something I need
to talk to you about.

04:59.608 --> 05:00.574
Sit down.

05:00.609 --> 05:03.377
What is it?

05:03.412 --> 05:05.112
I just got a visit
from Sean Cahill.

05:05.147 --> 05:06.446
About Gallo?

05:06.482 --> 05:07.959
I thought you said
he can't get him transferred.

05:07.983 --> 05:09.549
He can't, but it turns out

05:09.585 --> 05:10.795
there's a way
he can get you out.

05:10.819 --> 05:11.919
What do you mean "out"?

05:11.954 --> 05:15.055
I mean out, as in
you walk out that front door

05:15.090 --> 05:17.324
and you never look back.

05:17.359 --> 05:18.792
- What's the catch?
- Mike--

05:18.827 --> 05:20.872
Harvey, you're not here
telling me that I can get out

05:20.896 --> 05:21.862
with that look on your face

05:21.897 --> 05:23.074
if there isn't something else.

05:23.098 --> 05:24.665
He needs you to inform
on your cellmate.

05:24.700 --> 05:25.732
What?

05:25.768 --> 05:27.178
If whatever you get
leads to a conviction

05:27.202 --> 05:28.368
on his father-in-law,

05:28.404 --> 05:30.671
he'll commute your sentence
and you get to walk.

05:32.341 --> 05:34.107
- What'd the guy do?
- Who cares what he did?

05:34.143 --> 05:35.676
I care,
because if it was so bad,

05:35.711 --> 05:37.255
why didn't Kevin turn on him
in the first place?

05:37.279 --> 05:38.245
Mike, what does it matter?

05:38.280 --> 05:39.280
He can get you out.

05:39.315 --> 05:41.114
This is my only
friend in here.

05:41.150 --> 05:42.115
I'm not gonna betray him.

05:42.151 --> 05:43.684
Friend?
Listen to me, God damn it.

05:43.719 --> 05:45.519
There's someone in here
trying to kill you

05:45.554 --> 05:46.720
and I'm giving you a way out.

05:46.755 --> 05:47.755
I'm taking care of Gallo.

05:47.790 --> 05:49.000
What the hell is that
supposed to mean?

05:49.024 --> 05:50.602
It means that I did
what you told me to do.

05:50.626 --> 05:52.671
I threatened to tell people
that he was an informant,

05:52.695 --> 05:55.028
but what I also did was found
out a way to get him parole.

05:55.064 --> 05:56.763
Parole?
Are you crazy?

05:56.799 --> 05:58.098
He's not gonna get parole.

05:58.133 --> 05:59.099
Who's gonna say he deserves it?

05:59.134 --> 06:00.167
You know what, Harvey?

06:00.202 --> 06:01.546
Instead of coming here
and telling me

06:01.570 --> 06:03.381
to betray my cellmate because
Gallo will never get parole,

06:03.405 --> 06:05.083
maybe you should be helping
me get it for him.

06:05.107 --> 06:07.274
I'm never helping that
piece of shit do anything,

06:07.309 --> 06:09.242
and this isn't about Gallo
and you know it.

06:09.278 --> 06:11.556
No, it's about you telling me
to turn on the one guy in here

06:11.580 --> 06:13.780
that I trust based on
some plan that Cahill has

06:13.816 --> 06:15.026
that we don't even
know will work.

06:15.050 --> 06:16.283
No, Mike.

06:16.318 --> 06:18.296
It's about giving you
a chance to get your life back

06:18.320 --> 06:20.921
while it still looks the same.

06:20.956 --> 06:23.423
Now, are you going
to take it or not?

06:25.327 --> 06:28.996
<i>♪ See the money,</i>
<i>wanna stay for your meal ♪</i>

06:29.031 --> 06:32.332
<i>♪ Get another piece of pie</i>
<i>for your wife ♪</i>

06:32.368 --> 06:35.502
<i>♪ Everybody wanna know</i>
<i>how it feel ♪</i>

06:35.537 --> 06:39.272
<i>♪ Everybody wanna see</i>
<i>what it's like ♪</i>

06:39.308 --> 06:42.476
<i>♪ I'll even eat a bean pie,</i>
<i>I don't mind ♪</i>

06:42.511 --> 06:46.179
<i>♪ Me and Missy is</i>
<i>so busy, busy making money ♪</i>

06:46.215 --> 06:47.647
<i>♪ All right ♪</i>

06:47.683 --> 06:49.217
<i>♪ All step back,</i>
<i>I'm 'bout to dance ♪</i>

